        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>
            <button class="faq-toggle" aria-expanded="false">
              <span class="faq-icon"></span>
              How does the R5 II compare to the Nikon Z8?
            </button>
          </h3>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>
              Both are exceptional flagships. R5 II adds Eye Control AF as a unique differentiator. Z8 has slightly better video specs and lighter body. Choose based on lens ecosystemâ€”both deliver professional results.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>
            <button class="faq-toggle" aria-expanded="false">
              <span class="faq-icon"></span>
              Has the overheating issue been fixed?
            </button>
          </h3>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>
              Completely resolved. Canon redesigned internal cooling. 8K 30p records 90+ minutes continuously. Even 8K 60p sustains 45-60 minute takes. Overheating is no longer a practical concern.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>
            <button class="faq-toggle" aria-expanded="false">
              <span class="faq-icon"></span>
              Does Eye Control AF work reliably?
            </button>
          </h3>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>
              Yes, after proper calibration (5-10 minutes). Accuracy is approximately 85-90%. Works best for single-point AF and subject detection. Most users find it transformative for fast-paced shooting.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>
            <button class="faq-toggle" aria-expanded="false">
              <span class="faq-icon"></span>
              Who should buy the Canon R5 Mark II?
            </button>
          </h3>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>
              Professional photographers and videographers needing maximum versatility. Excels for commercial, fashion, weddings, wildlife, and video production. Skip if budget-conscious or focused on one discipline.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Author Box -->
